  "description": "<p>Use this oracle to determine the placement of a planet around its stellar object. To use it...</p><ul><li>Calculate the number of orbits that are currently free--in which no planet or megastructure has been marked - and reference the corresponding column.</li><li>Mark the planet in the resulting free planetary orbit. These are numbered as per their proximity to the stellar object - the 1st being the closest one.</li><li>Shift one column to the right as the number of free planetary orbits changes and there are planets left to place.</li></ul>",
